The Commission consists of the following 34 voting members appointed by the Governor:
7 individuals, 1 from each of the following 7 counties, on the recommendation of the governing body of that county:
Anne Arundel County;
Calvert County;
Charles County;
Howard County;
Montgomery County;
Prince George's County; and
St. Mary's County;
1 individual representing the Washington Suburban Sanitary Commission;
1 individual from each of the following regional planning agencies:
the Maryland-National Capital Park and Planning Commission, Montgomery County;
the Maryland-National Capital Park and Planning Commission, Prince George's County; and
the Tri-County Council for Southern Maryland;
1 individual, representing a municipality in the watershed, on the recommendation of the corresponding governing body of that municipality;
1 individual representing a large federal facility in the watershed;
as far as possible, the following individuals appointed by the Governor with the advice and consent of the Senate, shall be selected to represent broad geographic, economic, and social interests within the watershed:
2 individuals representing farming interests;
1 individual representing business interests;
4 individuals representing environmental and citizen interests;
2 individuals representing developer interests;
2 individuals representing academic interests;
2 individuals, 1 each, representing 2 soil conservation districts;
1 individual representing the University of Maryland Cooperative Extension Service; and
1 individual representing watermen interests; and
as ex officio members:
the Secretary of Agriculture or a designee;
the Secretary of the Environment or a designee;
the Secretary of Natural Resources or a designee;
the Secretary of Planning or a designee;
the Secretary of Transportation or a designee; and
the Chief of the Planning Division, U.S. Army Corps of Engineers, Baltimore District or a designee.
